# CampusReport
An Android application designed to allow students to report issues and incidents occurring within the school environment using camera and location sensors
The application enables students to submit complaints such as broken chairs, water leakage, electrical faults, sanitation problems, or security concerns. Students can capture images of the issue using the phone camera and record a voice description using the microphone, which will be converted into text or saved as audio for clarity.

The system stores all reports in a database where administrators can view, review, and update the status of each complaint (Pending, In Progress, Resolved). Administrators can also manage users and track resolved issues.

The application aims to improve communication between students and school management, ensure faster response to problems, and maintain a better campus environment.
